---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout title="The Blueprint for a Calm Puppy">
  <!-- MAIN CONTENT -->

  <!-- MAIN CONTENT -->
  <main class="max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <!-- HERO SECTION -->
    <section class="mb-16">
      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <div class="text-center mb-8">
          <span
            class="text-green-600 font-bold text-sm uppercase tracking-wider"
            >Programs</span
          >
          <h1
            class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-gray-900 mt-2 mb-4 leading-tight"
          >
            Puppy Starter Program
          </h1>
          <div class="flex justify-center gap-3 mb-6">
            <span class="tag">3 Weeks</span>
            <span class="tag">2 Weeks Board & Train</span>
            <span class="tag">1 Week Handler Coaching</span>
          </div>
          <p class="text-3xl font-bold text-green-600 mb-4">
            "Start Strong. Build for Life."
          </p>
          <p
            class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 max-w-4xl mx-auto leading-relaxed"
          >
            A <strong>3-week immersive training experience</strong> that gives your
            puppy the best possible foundation for life. Your pup stays with us for
            <strong>2 weeks of intensive training</strong>, then comes home for <strong
              >1 week of hands-on handler coaching</strong
            >—ensuring both you and your puppy succeed together.
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-600 mt-4">
            <strong>Perfect for Puppies 5-9 Months Old</strong> • Serving Bassett
            & Southwest Virginia • <a
              href="tel:+12762292625"
              class="text-green-600 hover:underline font-semibold"
              >(276) 229-2625</a
            >
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Quick CTA Buttons -->
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center mt-8">
          <a
            href="#week-by-week"
            class="bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700 text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-full text-lg transition transform hover:scale-105 text-center"
          >
            See 3-Week Breakdown
          </a>
          <a
            href="https://leashlegacyk9.com/contact/"
            class="bg-gray-900 hover:bg-gray-800 text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-full text-lg border-2 border-gray-900 transition text-center"
          >
            Schedule a Consultation
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- THE GOAL -->
    <section
      class="mb-20 bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 py-16 px-4 rounded-2xl"
    >
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
        <div class="text-5xl mb-6">🎯</div>
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">The Goal</h2>
        <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-lg">
          <p class="text-2xl text-gray-800 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
            Your puppy leaves with a <strong class="text-green-700"
              >calm default state</strong
            >, basic obedience, and an unshakeable foundation.
          </p>
          <p class="text-2xl text-gray-800 leading-relaxed">
            You leave knowing <strong class="text-green-700"
              >exactly how to continue building.</strong
            >
          </p>
        </div>
        <p class="text-gray-700 mt-6 text-lg italic">
          This isn't just puppy training. It's building the relationship that
          will last a lifetime.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHAT'S INCLUDED -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-12 text-center">
        What's Included in Your 3-Week Program
      </h2>

      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 lg:grid-cols-3 gap-6 mb-8">
        <div
          class="feature-card bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md border-t-4 border-green-500"
        >
          <div class="text-4xl mb-4">🏠</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
            2 Weeks Live-In Board & Train
          </h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
            Your puppy stays with us, trains daily, and learns structure in a
            real-world environment with proper nervous system regulation.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="feature-card bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md border-t-4 border-blue-500"
        >
          <div class="text-4xl mb-4">📹</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
            Daily Video Lessons
          </h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
            10-15 minute educational videos sent each morning so you're learning
            alongside your pup throughout the program.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="feature-card bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md border-t-4 border-purple-500"
        >
          <div class="text-4xl mb-4">📝</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
            Homework Assignments
          </h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
            2x daily practice exercises (10-15 minutes each) so you're ready for
            the handoff in week 3.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="feature-card bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md border-t-4 border-yellow-500"
        >
          <div class="text-4xl mb-4">🎓</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
            6+ Hands-On Sessions
          </h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
            3 sessions during weeks 1-2 (trainer + owner transfer) and 3-5
            sessions in week 3 (at-home coaching).
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="feature-card bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md border-t-4 border-red-500"
        >
          <div class="text-4xl mb-4">📖</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
            Custom Training Plan
          </h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
            Detailed written guide and take-home resources specific to YOUR
            puppy for continuing training after graduation.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div
          class="feature-card bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md border-t-4 border-indigo-500"
        >
          <div class="text-4xl mb-4">💬</div>
          <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Ongoing Support</h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 text-sm">
            Text, email, and phone support throughout the program and one month
            of follow-up support after graduation.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="bg-green-50 border-2 border-green-300 p-6 rounded-xl">
        <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3 text-center">
          Plus: Weekly Progress Updates
        </h3>
        <p class="text-gray-700 text-center max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          You'll receive photos, videos, and detailed progress reports
          throughout the 2-week board & train so you're never left wondering how
          your puppy is doing.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PROGRAM STRUCTURE OVERVIEW -->
    <section class="mb-20 bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-xl p-8 md:p-12">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8 text-center">
        How the Program Works
      </h2>

      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
          <div
            class="text-center p-6 bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 rounded-xl"
          >
            <div
              class="bg-green-600 text-white w-16 h-16 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-2xl font-bold mx-auto mb-4"
            >
              1-2
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Weeks 1-2</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3 font-semibold">
              Intensive Board & Train
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
              Your puppy stays with us for full immersion training. We build
              foundation, structure, and calm behavior through science-based
              methods.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div
            class="text-center p-6 bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 rounded-xl"
          >
            <div
              class="bg-blue-600 text-white w-16 h-16 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-2xl font-bold mx-auto mb-4"
            >
              3
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">Week 3</h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3 font-semibold">
              Home Transition & Handler Coaching
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
              Your puppy comes home! We shift focus to YOU with 3-5 hands-on
              coaching sessions teaching you to lead with confidence.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div
            class="text-center p-6 bg-gradient-to-br from-purple-50 to-pink-50 rounded-xl"
          >
            <div
              class="bg-purple-600 text-white w-16 h-16 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-2xl font-bold mx-auto mb-4"
            >
              +
            </div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
              After Graduation
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700 mb-3 font-semibold">Continued Success</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
              One month of follow-up support plus lifetime access to guidance.
              You're never left alone after the program ends.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WEEK-BY-WEEK BREAKDOWN -->
    <section id="week-by-week" class="mb-20">
      <div class="text-center mb-12">
        <h2 class="text-4xl md:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
          The 3-Week Journey
        </h2>
        <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 max-w-3xl mx-auto">
          Here's exactly what happens each week. Remember: <strong
            >every puppy learns at their own pace</strong
          >, so we adjust based on temperament, age, and developmental stage.
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="space-y-8">
        <!-- Week 1 -->
        <div class="week-card bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-md">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div
              class="bg-green-600 text-white w-20 h-20 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-3xl font-bold flex-shrink-0"
            >
              W1
            </div>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                Week 1 — Foundations & Trust
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 text-lg">
                <em
                  >Building the foundation for everything that follows: trust,
                  communication, and confidence.</em
                >
              </p>

              <div class="bg-green-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-6">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-green-900 mb-3 text-lg">
                  What Your Puppy Learns:
                </h4>
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                  <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
                    <li>✓ <strong>Name recognition & eye contact</strong></li>
                    <li>✓ <strong>Sit, Down, and Place</strong> (mat work)</li>
                    <li>
                      ✓ <strong>Intro to recall</strong> (coming when called)
                    </li>
                    <li>✓ <strong>Loose leash walking basics</strong></li>
                  </ul>
                  <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
                    <li>✓ <strong>Engagement games</strong></li>
                    <li>✓ <strong>Reward timing fundamentals</strong></li>
                    <li>✓ <strong>Confidence building</strong></li>
                    <li>✓ <strong>Calm default state foundation</strong></li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-6">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-blue-900 mb-3 text-lg">
                  What You'll Do:
                </h4>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
                  <li>
                    📹 <strong>Watch daily 10-15 minute video lessons</strong> — Topics:
                    "How Puppies Learn," "Leash Handling Basics," "Building Focus
                    in Distractions"
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    📝 <strong>Complete homework assignments</strong> (10-15 min,
                    2x/day) — Sit/Down practice, engagement games, structured walks
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    🎓 <strong>Attend 3 hands-on training sessions</strong> — Work
                    directly with your pup and trainer, learn reward timing and leash
                    handling
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div
                class="bg-gradient-to-r from-green-50 to-emerald-50 border-l-4 border-green-500 p-4 rounded"
              >
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-green-900">
                  <strong>Week 1 Goal:</strong> Build trust, establish clear communication,
                  and teach your puppy (and you!) the basics of the training game.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Week 2 -->
        <div class="week-card bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-md">
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div
              class="bg-green-600 text-white w-20 h-20 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-3xl font-bold flex-shrink-0"
            >
              W2
            </div>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                Week 2 — Structure & Early Reliability
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 text-lg">
                <em
                  >Building duration, adding distractions, and proofing skills
                  in real-world environments.</em
                >
              </p>

              <div class="bg-green-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-6">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-green-900 mb-3 text-lg">
                  What Your Puppy Learns:
                </h4>
                <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
                  <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
                    <li>
                      ✓ <strong>Increased duration</strong> in Sit, Down, Place
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      ✓ <strong>Heel position</strong> and structured walking
                    </li>
                    <li>✓ <strong>Long-line recall outdoors</strong></li>
                    <li>
                      ✓ <strong>Distraction proofing</strong> (toys, people, noise)
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                  <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
                    <li>
                      ✓ <strong>Real-world practice</strong> in parks and neighborhoods
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      ✓ <strong>Calm decision-making</strong> under pressure
                    </li>
                    <li>✓ <strong>Confidence in new environments</strong></li>
                    <li>✓ <strong>Nervous system regulation</strong></li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-6">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-blue-900 mb-3 text-lg">
                  What You'll Do:
                </h4>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
                  <li>
                    📹 <strong>Watch daily video lessons</strong> — Topics: "Recall
                    Games," "Proofing Cues at Home," "Strategic Use of Rewards," "Confidence
                    Building"
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    📝 <strong>Continue homework practice</strong> — Place + recall
                    indoors, heel games, outdoor recall, confidence exercises
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    🎓 <strong>Attend 3 more hands-on sessions</strong> — Learn strategic
                    reward use and refine your handling technique
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div
                class="bg-gradient-to-r from-green-50 to-emerald-50 border-l-4 border-green-500 p-4 rounded"
              >
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-green-900">
                  <strong>Week 2 Goal:</strong> Build reliability and duration in
                  all commands. Proof skills under real-world distractions.
                </p>
              </div>

              <div
                class="mt-6 p-4 bg-yellow-50 border-2 border-yellow-300 rounded-lg"
              >
                <p class="text-sm text-gray-800">
                  <strong>End of Week 2:</strong> Full graduation review with owner
                  covering Sit, Down, Place, Recall, and Leash Manners. You'll receive
                  your custom training plan and video: "Maintaining Progress."
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Week 3 -->
        <div
          class="week-card bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-md border-2 border-blue-300"
        >
          <div class="flex items-start gap-4">
            <div
              class="bg-blue-600 text-white w-20 h-20 rounded-full flex items-center justify-center text-3xl font-bold flex-shrink-0"
            >
              W3
            </div>
            <div class="flex-1">
              <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                Week 3 — Home Transition & Handler Coaching
              </h3>
              <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 text-lg">
                <em
                  ><strong>Your puppy comes home!</strong> This is where the real
                  work happens for YOU.</em
                >
              </p>

              <div
                class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-400 p-6 rounded-lg mb-6"
              >
                <h4 class="font-bold text-red-900 mb-2 text-lg">
                  ⚠️ Important Truth
                </h4>
                <p class="text-gray-800">
                  A perfectly trained puppy with an unprepared owner will
                  regress. Your puppy's success depends on you understanding
                  what we taught them and maintaining consistency. <strong
                    >That's why handler coaching isn't optional—it's essential.</strong
                  >
                </p>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-blue-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-6">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-blue-900 mb-3 text-lg">
                  What Happens This Week:
                </h4>

                <div class="mb-6">
                  <h5 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                    Days 1-2: Intensive Training
                  </h5>
                  <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700 ml-4">
                    <li>
                      • <strong>Live demonstrations</strong> of every command your
                      puppy knows
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      • <strong>YOU practice while we coach</strong> (not watching—doing)
                    </li>
                    <li>• <strong>Video reviews</strong> of your technique</li>
                    <li>
                      • <strong>Real-world walks</strong> and exposure work (park,
                      neighborhood, car)
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      • <strong>House routine setup</strong> — feeding structure,
                      crate management, potty breaks
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </div>

                <div>
                  <h5 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                    Days 3-5: Real-World Application
                  </h5>
                  <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700 ml-4">
                    <li>• You take your puppy home (we're still coaching)</li>
                    <li>
                      • We observe your home setup and provide recommendations
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      • <strong>Troubleshooting real issues</strong> as they come
                      up
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      • We identify YOUR personal challenges and solve them
                      together
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      • Final walk, final questions, final confidence building
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>

              <div class="bg-green-50 p-6 rounded-lg mb-6">
                <h4 class="font-bold text-green-900 mb-3 text-lg">
                  What You'll Leave With:
                </h4>
                <ul class="space-y-2 text-sm text-gray-700">
                  <li>
                    ✓ <strong>Detailed written guide</strong> specific to YOUR puppy
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    ✓ <strong
                      >Videos of you handling your puppy correctly</strong>
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    ✓ <strong>Daily routine calendar</strong> ready to print and use
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    ✓ <strong>Emergency troubleshooting plan</strong> for common issues
                  </li>
                  <li>
                    ✓ <strong>One month of follow-up phone support</strong> (included)
                  </li>
                </ul>
              </div>

              <div
                class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 border-l-4 border-blue-500 p-4 rounded"
              >
                <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-blue-900">
                  <strong>Week 3 Goal:</strong> You leave with confidence, a clear
                  plan, and the ability to maintain and build on what your puppy learned.
                  You're never alone after this.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div
        class="mt-12 p-8 bg-gradient-to-r from-green-50 to-emerald-50 border-2 border-green-300 rounded-xl"
      >
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 text-center">
          Throughout All 3 Weeks
        </h3>
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl text-center">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-2">📹</div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Daily Video Lessons</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
              Educational content sent each morning
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl text-center">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-2">📸</div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Progress Updates</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
              Photos, videos, and detailed reports
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl text-center">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-2">💬</div>
            <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">Direct Support</p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600">
              Text/email for questions anytime
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHAT PUPPY LEARNS (COMPREHENSIVE) -->
    <section class="mb-20 bg-white rounded-2xl shadow-xl p-8 md:p-12">
      <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8 text-center">
        What Your Puppy Actually Learns
      </h2>

      <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-8 mb-8">
          <div
            class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-indigo-50 p-6 rounded-xl"
          >
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
              Foundation Behaviors
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold">•</span>
                <span
                  ><strong>Sit, Down, Stay</strong> — Impulse control on command</span
                >
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold">•</span>
                <span
                  ><strong>Loose Leash Walking</strong> — Real-world walking without
                  pulling</span
                >
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold">•</span>
                <span
                  ><strong>Recall Foundation</strong> — Coming when called (even with
                  distractions)</span
                >
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold">•</span>
                <span
                  ><strong>Crate Comfort</strong> — Safe den behavior, independent
                  rest</span
                >
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold">•</span>
                <span
                  ><strong>Calm Feeding</strong> — No begging, no resource guarding,
                  structure</span
                >
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold">•</span>
                <span
                  ><strong>Bite Inhibition</strong> — Soft mouth, appropriate play</span
                >
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-blue-600 font-bold">•</span>
                <span
                  ><strong>Confidence Building</strong> — Calm response to new environments</span
                >
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div
            class="bg-gradient-to-br from-green-50 to-emerald-50 p-6 rounded-xl"
          >
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
              Nervous System Work
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-3 text-gray-700">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-green-600 font-bold">•</span>
                <span
                  ><strong>Calm default state</strong> (not hyper-vigilant)</span
                >
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-2">
                <span class="text-green-600 font-bold">•</span>
                <span
